<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1679,2028]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,464]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1977786296" collectionCode="USSR" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" location="South America" municipality="Zakovska" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" specimenCount="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1679,1704]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks</emphasis>
. The genus was established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[674,841,1679,1704]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Berlese, A. (1889) Acari, Myriopoda et Scorpiones hucusque in Italia reperta. Tipografia del Seminario, Padova, 52 pp." type="book" year="1889">Berlese (1889)</bibRefCitation>
to include the single species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1889" box="[1188,1329,1679,1704]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Haemogamasus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis box="[1188,1222,1680,1703]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Hg</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1239,1329,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the European mole (
<figureCitation box="[340,407,1715,1740]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1612,1634]" captionTargetBox="[502,1109,828,1575]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[478,1109,810,1588]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Haemogamasus hirsutus, the type species of the genus Haemogamasus (after Berlese, 1889)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/818305/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). This species has not been found in Asiatic 
<collectingCountry box="[927,1002,1715,1740]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Russia</collectingCountry>
although numerous recordings of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1889" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Haemogamasus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis box="[1395,1429,1716,1739]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Hg</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,241,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the European part of the former 
<collectionCode box="[679,749,1751,1775]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">USSR</collectionCode>
are known (
<bibRefCitation author="Nikulina" box="[892,1067,1751,1776]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Nikulina, N. A. (2004) A catalogue of parasitic Gamasina mites of mammals of Northern Eurasia (Russia). Aktsioner &amp; Co, Saint-Petersburg, 170 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="2004">Nikulina, 2004</bibRefCitation>
). The most important taxonomic works on the genus are those by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vitzthum" box="[522,711,1787,1812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Vitzthum, H. (1930) Milben als Pesttrager? Zoologischer Jahrbucher. Abteilung fur Systematik, Okologie und Geographie der Tiere, 60, 381 - 428." type="journal article" year="1930">Vitzthum (1930)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bregetova" box="[724,914,1787,1812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Bregetova, N. G. (1949) Materials on the fauna of mites of the family Haemogamasidae. Parazitologicheskiy sbornik Zoologicheskogo Instituta Akademii Nauk SSSR, 11, 161 - 185. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1949">Bregetova (1949</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bregetova" box="[927,999,1787,1812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Bregetova, N. G. (1956 a) Gamasid mites (Gamasoidea). Opredeliteli po faune SSSR, izdavaemye Zoologicheskim Institutom Akademii Nauk SSSR, 61, 1 - 247. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1956" yearSuffix="a">1956a</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Keegan" box="[1019,1189,1787,1812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Keegan, H. L. (1951) The mites of the subfamily Haemogamasinae (Acari: Laelaptidae). Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 101, 203 - 268." type="journal article" year="1951">Keegan (1951)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1201,1431,1787,1812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Evans, G. O. &amp; Till, W. M. (1966) Studies on the British Dermanyssidae (Acari: Mesostigmata). Part II. Classification. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Zoology, 14, 107 - 370." type="journal article" year="1966">Evans &amp; Till (1966)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Allred" box="[151,310,1823,1848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Allred, D. M. (1969) Haemogamasid mites of Eastern Asia and Western Pacific with a key to species. Journal of Medical Entomology, 6, 103 - 108." type="journal article" year="1969">Allred (1969)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[325,583,1823,1848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Williams, G. L., Smiley, R. L. &amp; Redington, B. C. (1978) A taxonomic study of the genus Haemogamasus in North America, with descriptions of two new species (Acari: Mesostigmata, Laelaptidae). International Journal of Acarology, 4, 235 - 273. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01647957808683122" type="journal article">
Williams 
<emphasis box="[437,490,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al</emphasis>
. (1978)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Haitlinger" box="[599,800,1823,1848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Haitlinger, R. (1988) Haemogamasidae Oudemans, 1926 (Acari, Mesostigmata) of Poland. Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne, 58, 635 - 662." type="journal article" year="1988">Haitlinger (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundquist" box="[866,1067,1823,1848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Lundquist, L. (1990) Taxonomic and functional significance of the presternal area in Haemogamasus mites (Acari- Mesostigmata: Laelaptidae), with a revised key to Fennoscandian species. Entomologia Scandinavia, 21, 329 - 337. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631290 X 00256" type="journal article" year="1990">Lundquist (1990)</bibRefCitation>
. The species of the genus were thought to inhabit all continents, except 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB0423DFDA1F8C7FCECF888" box="[630,803,1859,1884]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="South America" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">South America</location>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bregetova" box="[823,1031,1859,1884]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Bregetova, N. G. (1956 a) Gamasid mites (Gamasoidea). Opredeliteli po faune SSSR, izdavaemye Zoologicheskim Institutom Akademii Nauk SSSR, 61, 1 - 247. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1956" yearSuffix="a">Bregetova, 1956a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[1047,1299,1859,1884]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Williams, G. L., Smiley, R. L. &amp; Redington, B. C. (1978) A taxonomic study of the genus Haemogamasus in North America, with descriptions of two new species (Acari: Mesostigmata, Laelaptidae). International Journal of Acarology, 4, 235 - 273. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01647957808683122" type="journal article" year="1978">
Williams 
<emphasis box="[1160,1214,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al</emphasis>
., 1978
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundquist" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Lundquist, L. (1990) Taxonomic and functional significance of the presternal area in Haemogamasus mites (Acari- Mesostigmata: Laelaptidae), with a revised key to Fennoscandian species. Entomologia Scandinavia, 21, 329 - 337. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631290 X 00256" type="journal article" year="1990">Lundquist, 1990</bibRefCitation>
), but later records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1889" box="[455,634,1896,1919]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Haemogamasus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[455,634,1896,1919]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Haemogamasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[704,815,1895,1920]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[872,933,1895,1920]" name="Chile" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Chile</collectingCountry>
have now been published (
<bibRefCitation author="Mosquera" box="[1243,1431,1895,1919]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Mosquera, S. (1988) Eucheyletia hardyi Baker, 1949 y Haemogamasus pontiger (Berlese, 1904), dos acaros nuevos para la fauna Argentina. Neotropica, 34, 73 - 76." type="journal article" year="1988">Mosquera, 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Casanueva" box="[151,423,1931,1956]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Casanueva, M. E., Berrios, A. M., Peredo, A. A. A. &amp; Martinez, R. I. (1994) Mites associated on horses stables I. Androlaelaps casalis (Berlese), Haemogamasus horridus Michael and Proctolaelaps pygmaeus (Muller), the first record for Chile and redescription of the male (Acari: Mesostigmata). Gayana Zoologia, 58, 61 - 69." type="journal article" year="1994">
Casanueva 
<emphasis box="[284,338,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al</emphasis>
., 1994
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Herrin" box="[438,691,1931,1956]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Herrin, C. S. &amp; Sage, R. D. (2012) Description of a new species of Haemogamasus (Mesostigmata, Laelapidae, Haemogamasinae) from Chubut, Rio Negro and Neuquen Provinces, Argentina. Zookeys, 173, 51 - 77. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 173.1592" type="journal article" year="2012">Herrin &amp; Sage, 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The genus includes about 60 species, 12 of which have been recorded in Europe (Mašán &amp; Fend’a, 2010) and nearly 30 species in the former 
<collectionCode box="[1124,1194,1967,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">USSR</collectionCode>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Senotrusova" box="[1213,1431,1967,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Senotrusova, V. G. (1987) Gamasid mites - parasites of wild animals in Kazakhstan. Nauka, Alma-Ata, 224 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1987">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB0423DFB6AF82BFA83F813" box="[1213,1356,1967,1991]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Senotrusova" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Senotrusova</location>
, 1987
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Goncharova" box="[151,449,2003,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Goncharova, A. A., Bondarchuk, A. S. &amp; Vershinina, O. N. (1991) Gamasid mites - Ectoparasites of Mammals in Transbaikalia. Chita State Medical University, Chita, 121 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1991">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB0423DFF40F857FEEFF838" box="[151,288,2003,2028]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Goncharova" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Goncharova</location>
<emphasis box="[303,360,2003,2028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al</emphasis>
., 1991
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB0423DFE0AF857FDC3F83F" box="[477,524,2003,2027]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="One" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">One</location>
of these species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1904" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1904" box="[753,1103,2003,2028]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Haemogamasus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontiger">
<emphasis box="[753,787,2004,2027]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Hg</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[810,905,2004,2027]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">pontiger</emphasis>
(Berlese, 1904)
</taxonomicName>
, is of almost cosmopolitan distribution, being recorded from the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFD8AFF13FD12FF64" box="[605,733,151,176]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Old World" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Old World</location>
, the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFCC8FF13FC42FF64" box="[799,909,151,176]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Americas" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Americas</location>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[927,1044,151,176]" name="Antarctica" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1112,1214,151,176]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lundquist" box="[1236,1431,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refString="Lundquist, L. (1990) Taxonomic and functional significance of the presternal area in Haemogamasus mites (Acari- Mesostigmata: Laelaptidae), with a revised key to Fennoscandian species. Entomologia Scandinavia, 21, 329 - 337. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631290 X 00256" type="journal article" year="1990">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFB03FF13FA85FF64" box="[1236,1354,151,176]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Lundquist" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Lundquist</location>
, 1990
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Halliday" box="[151,321,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refString="Halliday, B. (2011) Occurrence of the predatory mite Haemogamasus pontiger (Berlese) (Acari: Laelapidae) in Australia, with a review of its biology. Australian Journal of Entomology, 50, 61 - 64." type="journal article" year="2011">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFF40FF38FF36FF01" box="[151,249,188,213]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Halliday" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Halliday</location>
, 2011
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFE80FF38FE29FF01" box="[343,486,188,213]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Ecologically" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Ecologically</location>
, most species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1889" box="[688,867,189,212]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Haemogamasus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[688,867,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Haemogamasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are parasites of small mammals and abundant in their hosts’ nests and shelters (
<bibRefCitation author="Balashov" box="[495,674,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refString="Balashov, Yu. S. (2009) Acari and Insect Parasitism on Terrestrial Vertebrates. Nauka Publishers, Saint-Petersburg, 358 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="2009">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFE38FF5BFD95FF2C" box="[495,602,223,248]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Balashov" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Balashov</location>
, 2009
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFD62FF64FD03FF23" box="[693,716,224,247]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="In" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">In</location>
general, these mites are opportunistic parasites able to exploit a wide range of host species (
<bibRefCitation author="Bregetova" box="[485,681,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refString="Bregetova, N. G. (1949) Materials on the fauna of mites of the family Haemogamasidae. Parazitologicheskiy sbornik Zoologicheskogo Instituta Akademii Nauk SSSR, 11, 161 - 185. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1949">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFE32FE80FD93FEC8" box="[485,604,260,284]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Bregetova" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Bregetova</location>
, 1949
</bibRefCitation>
); some of them were collected also from birds and birds’ nests (
<bibRefCitation author="Haitlinger" box="[158,347,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refString="Haitlinger, R. (1988) Haemogamasidae Oudemans, 1926 (Acari, Mesostigmata) of Poland. Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne, 58, 635 - 662." type="journal article" year="1988">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFF49FEA3FEDCFE94" box="[158,275,295,320]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Haitlinger" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Haitlinger</location>
, 1988
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFEBFFEA3FDCDFE94" box="[360,514,295,320]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Gwaizdowicz" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Gwaizdowicz</location>
<emphasis box="[522,573,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al</emphasis>
., 2006). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFD73FEA3FD2FFE94" box="[676,736,295,320]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Strict" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Strict</location>
host specificity in the genus is rarely observed (
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFADEFEACFAB1FE94" box="[1289,1406,296,320]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Bregetova" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Bregetova</location>
&amp; 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFF40FEC8FF35FEB1" box="[151,250,332,357]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Nel'zina" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Nel’zina</location>
, 1952). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFE81FEC8FE59FEB0" box="[342,406,332,356]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Some" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Some</location>
taxa (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1904" box="[477,622,333,356]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Haemogamasus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontiger">
<emphasis box="[477,511,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Hg</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[527,622,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">pontiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are regarded as predators (
<bibRefCitation author="Halliday" box="[938,1108,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refString="Halliday, B. (2011) Occurrence of the predatory mite Haemogamasus pontiger (Berlese) (Acari: Laelapidae) in Australia, with a review of its biology. Australian Journal of Entomology, 50, 61 - 64." type="journal article" year="2011">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFC7DFEC8FBC2FEB1" box="[938,1037,332,357]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Halliday" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Halliday</location>
, 2011
</bibRefCitation>
), and their relationships with 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFF40FEEBFE9DFE5C" box="[151,338,367,392]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Micromammalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Micromammalia</location>
are rather indirect. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFDE1FEEBFDADFE5C" box="[566,610,367,392]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="The" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">The</location>
role of different 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1889" box="[808,987,369,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Haemogamasus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[808,987,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Haemogamasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species as vectors of viruses and other pathogenic microorganisms has been elucidated by many authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Zemskaya" box="[939,1134,404,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refString="Zemskaya, A. A. (1973) Parasitic Gamasid Mites and Their Medical Importance. Meditsina Publishing House, Moscow, 168 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1973">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFC7CFE10FBECFE79" box="[939,1059,404,429]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Zemskaya" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Zemskaya</location>
, 1973
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yakimenko" box="[1151,1431,404,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refString="Yakimenko, V. V., Dekonenko, A. Ye., Mal'kova, M. G., Kuz'min, I. V., Tantsev, A. K., Dzagurova, T. K. &amp; Tkachenko, Ye. A. (2000) Spread of hantaviruses in West Siberia. Meditsinskaya Parazitologiya i Parazitarnye Bolezni, 3, 21 - 28. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="2000">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFBA8FE10FB30FE79" box="[1151,1279,404,429]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Yakimenko" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Yakimenko</location>
<emphasis box="[1291,1346,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al</emphasis>
., 2000
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Valiente" box="[151,448,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refString="Valiente Moro, C., Chauve, C. &amp; Zenner, L. (2005) Vectorial role of some dermanyssoid mites (Acari, Mesostigmata, Dermanyssoidea). Parasite, 12, 99 - 109." type="journal article" year="2005">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C31742FFB0423AFF40FE10FC06FE04:8EB5F08FFFB7423AFF40FE33FEF7FE1B" box="[151,312,439,464]" country="Russia" county="Mi'tkova" municipality="Zakovska" name="Valiente Moro" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Valiente Moro</location>
<emphasis box="[319,368,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al</emphasis>
., 2005
</bibRefCitation>
; 
